f:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Crello is best suited for social media creators, small businesses, non designers, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Looka, meanwhile, shines for startups, entrepreneurs, small businesses, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2017, Crello describes itself as \"Online graphic design tool with animated templates and easy editing (now VistaCreate).\" Looka, established in 2016, positions itself as \"AI-powered logo maker and brand identity design platform.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
10:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Looka** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (7.0 vs 6.0). However, this does not mean Crello is a poor choice — far from it. Crello excels in its own right, particularly for social media creators and small businesses.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value quick ai-generated logo options, go with Looka. If good animated design templates matters more to you, Crello is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
